ects (such as paper and whisky)</p></scopecontent></c02><c02 id="aspace_b3f35a49693fab5919e3b589b36b12bf" level="item"><did><unittitle>Letter from C. W. Shepherd to "My dear Father"</unittitle><unitid>Item 4</unitid><unitdate calendar="gregorian" era="ce" normal="1862-05-04/1862-05-04">May 4, 1862</unitdate><container id="aspace_677142590d9c21800412ae9c66f28776" label="Mixed Materials [31924066575477]" type="box">1</container><container id="aspace_f54b64b9cf6ebcd73d8bc5415af16573" parent="aspace_677142590d9c21800412ae9c66f28776" type="folder">1</container></did><scopecontent id="aspace_f1801c35c8a31b12909d6224b0171e81"><head>Scope and Contents</head><p>Addressed from Reyk[j]avik. Mentions traveling.</p></scopecontent></c02><c02 id="aspace_a9185a9a9930bb44cce1b158759463b2" level="item"><did><unittitle>Letter from C. W. Shepherd to "My dear Father"</unittitle><unitid>Item 5</unitid><unitdate calendar="gregorian" era="ce" normal="1862-05-05/1862-05-05">May 5, 1862</unitdate><container id="aspace_aa8a8778da8c1bd8ca3f8285068e057c" label="Mixed Materials [31924066575477]" type="box">1</container><container id="aspace_1dd654906e07b24c77fdeb5eee4bef29" parent="aspace_aa8a8778da8c1bd8ca3f8285068e057c" type="folder">1</container></did><scopecontent id="aspace_10bd276ce4f8846ea1e3262c018462f2"><head>Scope and Contents</head><p>Mentions leaving from Reyk[j]avik that morning and traveling in Iceland.</p></scopecontent></c02><c02 id="aspace_ca5a3663c222d00e38a311348f9e7f85" level="item"><did><unittitle>Letter from C. W. Shepherd to "My dear Father"</unittitle><unitid>Item 6</unitid><unitdate calendar="gregorian" era="ce">May, 25, 1862</unitdate><container id="aspace_cc9c4d7937cc49b1c328f7b919808226" label="Mixed Materials [31924066575477]" type="box">1</container><container id="aspace_2957133c53bc0916c8f01eafd7eb361d" parent="aspace_cc9c4d7937cc49b1c328f7b919808226" type="folder">1</container></did><scopecontent id="aspace_6f43997a739d6b5b55d1691ef5a8b9e8"><head>Scope and Contents</head><p>Addressed from Thingnefs. Mentions the rain and snow of Iceland, continues discussion of travel.</p></scopecontent></c02><c02 id="aspace_c78b698d8d6075c78f5debf2356e5472" level="item"><did><unittitle>Letter "Accepted by Mr. Shepherd"</unittitle><unitid>Item 7</unitid><unitdate calendar="gregorian" era="ce" normal="1862-05-28/1862-05-28">May 28, 1862</unitdate><container id="aspace_65e207d72ed8a75da8608e62aaccb279" label="Mixed Materials [31924066575477]" type="box">1</container><container id="aspace_322d36204620d08d36bde9b6e85c48ef" parent="aspace_65e207d72ed8a75da8608e62aaccb279" type="folder">1</container></did><scopecontent id="aspace_2e130b1fcdecb44a1df736237340bd9c"><head>Scope and Contents</head><p>Mentions finances.</p></scopecontent></c02><c02 id="aspace_ed09fd563ee4f00b503c1097f3a5e98c" level="item"><did><unittitle>Letter from James Retcher to "My dear Shepherd"</unittitle><unitid>Item 8</unitid><unitdate calendar="gregorian" era="ce" normal="1862-08-25/1862-08-25">August 25, 1862</unitdate><container id="aspace_c72622d96abde8dadb65b3c2da3ff333" label="Mixed Materials [31924066575477]" type="box">1</container><container id="aspace_d46e9c20b326abdb412f3d92e826c840" parent="aspace_c72622d96abde8dadb65b3c2da3ff333" type="folder">1</container></did><scopecontent id="aspace_23c3f65b1636d65b233da1738a8cc405"><head>Scope and Contents</head><p>Addressed from Peterhead (presumably Scotland). Mentions a hurried message and difficulties with the post and travel.</p></scopecontent></c02><c02 id="aspace_871d7ba83814e719f70f333baed72799" level="item"><did><unittitle>Letter from O. V. Gislason to "My dear friend"</unittitle><unitid>Item 9</unitid><unitdate calendar="gregorian" era="ce" normal="1864-04-24/1864-04-24">April 24, 1864</unitdate><container id="aspace_57cb418de7c9ff5948b5071540846979" label="Mixed Materials [31924066575477]" type="box">1</container><container id="aspace_a3657062d4ae2fbda83dd8591d209b84" parent="aspace_57cb418de7c9ff5948b5071540846979" type="folder">1</container></did><scopecontent id="aspace_7b30fdec445b0978e8f833825f494373"><head>Scope and Contents</head><p>Addressed from Iceland. Mentions working on translating texts into Icelandic, asks for assistance to travel to England.</p></scopecontent></c02><c02 id="aspace_95f8444898535611fc3e6a9c6cb0ae5f" level="item"><did><unittitle>Letter from the Royal Geographical Society</unittitle><unitid>Item 10</unitid><unitdate calendar="gregorian" era="ce" normal="1867-03-19/1867-03-19">March 19, 1867</unitdate><container id="aspace_ad6f6c4f93e0187a8fd8c300ed825261" label="Mixed Materials [31924066575477]" type="box">1</container><container id="aspace_d15270998e0850e4463143bddeb44dd7" parent="aspace_ad6f6c4f93e0187a8fd8c300ed825261" type="folder">1</container></did><scopecontent id="aspace_66818ae5a017fe2ec8722f03d45c27e6"><head>Scope and Contents</head><p>Documents the receiving of<title> The North-West Peninsula of Iceland</title> and giving thanks for its donation to the Society.</p></scopecontent></c02><c02 id="aspace_e4c9c4c20ae41910dc9ad1bafcd1644a" level="item"><did><unittitle>Letter from the Zoological Society of London</unittitle><unitid>Item 11</unitid><unitdate calendar="gregorian" era="ce" normal="1867-03-21/1867-03-21">March 21, 1867</unitdate><container id="aspace_3a3234b7e62b6af77d6d11851d7f99fb" label="Mixed Materials [31924066575477]" type="box">1</container><container id="aspace_31a9f7a5d2c0d30bec593e02c29894fa" parent="aspace_3a3234b7e62b6af77d6d11851d7f99fb" type="folder">1</container></did><scopecontent id="aspace_b4ec13283325ee9924a2db685c294121"><head>Scope and Contents</head><p>Gives thanks for the gift of <title>The North-West Peninsula of Iceland</title> to the library.</p></scopecontent></c02><c02 id="aspace_b51a93fa4da1783459c37d8fb95e762d" level="item"><did><unittitle>Letter from W. M. James to "My dear Shepherd"</unittitle><unitid>Item 12</unitid><unitdate calendar="gregorian" era="ce" normal="1868-04-09/1868-04-09">April 9, 1868</unitdate><container id="aspace_8ec8ad2d8b732b1da4d229b3bcee99b6" label="Mixed Materials [31924066575477]" type="box">1</container><container id="aspace_f44acdaf4a2e5fe5e765ed81fed59ca8" parent="aspace_8ec8ad2d8b732b1da4d229b3bcee99b6" type="folder">1</container></did><scopecontent id="aspace_6f43c80c262adf24c9f5bef32207fd98"><head>Scope and Contents</head><p>Addressed from Fürstenbad. Discusses Shepherd's book (<title>The North-West Peninsula of Iceland</title>).</p></scopecontent></c02><c02 id="aspace_8376996033eae2c088be2ee61ccb00cc" level="item"><did><unittitle>Letter to Cheriton Bickley Kent from Kenny Mac Cormac</unittitle><unitid>Item 13</unitid><unitdate calendar="gregorian" era="ce" normal="1870-07-21/1870-07-21">July 21, 1870</unitdate><container id="aspace_b24744d069a6922fb4771889e4cc6498" label="Mixed Materials [31924066575477]" type="box">1</container><container id="aspace_73a433e758b7a2538fc762fe72ea0b0a" parent="aspace_b24744d069a6922fb4771889e4cc6498" type="folder">1</container></did><scopecontent id="aspace_e8faec7476a0408064032d19cb38cc25"><head>Scope and Contents</head><p>Discusses welding and mentions working in Iceland.</p></scopecontent></c02></c01><c01 id="aspace_a69403551b72a430f823569c3f3e0110" level="series"><did><unittitle>Series II. Newspaper Book Reviews</unittitle></did><c02 id="aspace_675a9ca687389d90c9a59094570b1b95" level="item"><did><unittitle><title>The Morning Star </title></unittitle><unitdate calendar="gregorian" era="ce" normal="1863-02-06/1863-02-06">February 6, 1863</unitdate><container id="aspace_842be1448f2525d49f13fac9ad1e34bf" label="Mixed Materials [31924088320639]" type="mapcase folder">1</container></did><scopecontent id="aspace_2122d4238dd2d321bd6a063d08ff5afd"><head>Scope and Contents</head><p>Contains advertisements, railway traffics, weather report, shipping intelligence, police and law intelligence.</p></scopecontent></c02><c02 id="aspace_8f014dd505acefa7d06a31c164505c07" level="item"><did><unittitle><title>Maidstone Telegraph</title> No. 419</unittitle><unitdate calendar="gregorian" era="ce" normal="1866-12-15/1866-12-15">December 15, 1866</unitdate><container id="aspace_7a23df6cf9cb7c37aede3db192635437" label="Mixed Materials [31924088320639]" type="mapcase folder">1</container></did><scopecontent id="aspace_69465eca55ea60c6d62c56e9c01696ca"><head>Scope and Contents</head><p>Samples of articles and topics: railway times, London markets, "Coroner's Inquiet," assorted advertisements, articles on trade unions, articles on education, police brutality, "The Paris Exhibition," "Death of a Vegetarian from Abstemiousness, "Discovery of a Skeleton in Ratcliffe Highway."</p></scopecontent></c02><c02 id="aspace_1ba430a45864430b1cc10c421303b25d" level="item"><did><unittitle><title>The Athenaeum:</title> Journal of English and Foreign Literature, Science, and the Fine Arts, London</unittitle><unitdate calendar="gregorian" era="ce" normal="1867-03-09/1867-03-09">March 9, 1867</unitdate><container id="aspace_4b43e6f71f7f629318157b3a84a01e00" label="Mixed Materials [31924066575477]" type="box">1</container><container id="aspace_6ff2c904a2a921f4fd575bb993333003" parent="aspace_4b43e6f71f7f629318157b3a84a01e00" type="folder">2</container></did><scopecontent id="aspace_9918642c582ec3dcd041c0a2f036eab4"><head>Scope and Contents</head><p>Among many others, contains a review of <title>The North-West Peninsula of Iceland</title>.</p></scopecontent></c02><c02 id="aspace_1f1d71c8cfb22c154604c224238a9705" level="item"><did><unittitle><title>Land and Water</title> Vol. 3 No. 60</unittitle><unitdate calendar="gregorian" era="ce" normal="1867-03-16/1867-03-16">March 16, 1867</unitdate><container id="aspace_b68cbff05e5e80d2e1adb18b6eb2cd15" label="Mixed Materials [31924088320639]" type="mapcase folder">1</container></did><scopecontent id="aspace_3a5788e59149284194dfa253b297feed"><head>Scope and Contents</head><p>Among many others, contains a review of <title>The North-West Peninsula of Iceland</title>.</p></scopecontent></c02><c02 id="aspace_1c0338521846abc8e7526f8f302cbbda" level="item"><did><unittitle>The Globe and Traveller<title> No. 21, 407, Evening</title></unittitle><unitdate calendar="gregorian" era="ce" normal="1867-03-11/1867-03-11">March 11, 1867</unitdate><container id="aspace_ee875e7cd6fa25534dc1ae83b48a5886" label="Mixed Materials [31924088320639]" type="mapcase folder">1</container></did><scopecontent id="aspace_ba6453aaf1d70eaf8fb953f22151baef"><head>Scope and Contents</head><p>Among many others, contains a review of <title>The North-West Peninsula of Iceland</title>.</p></scopecontent></c02><c02 id="aspace_3603aceb70f8822749679c1854fbde1c" level="item"><did><unittitle><title>Gardeners Chronicle</title></unittitle><unitdate calendar="gregorian" era="ce" normal="1867-03-16/1867-03-16">March 16, 1867</unitdate><container id="aspace_0e5a1b20511737c60bef3799eed1f8b9" label="Mixed Materials [31924066575477]" type="box">1</container><container id="aspace_b33d2ee00a6d407749d4e030c986a16c" parent="aspace_0e5a1b20511737c60bef3799eed1f8b9" type="folder">2</container></did><scopecontent id="aspace_e555f64fc266dcdca4f6814ad7704700"><head>Scope and Contents</head><p>Review of <title>The North-West Peninsula of Iceland</title>.</p></scopecontent></c02><c02 id="aspace_df760db0eaa932c5fdb3f5f2dfaa978e" level="item"><did><unittitle><title>Morning Herald</title></unittitle><unitdate calendar="gregorian" era="ce" normal="1867-04-04/1867-04-04">April 4, 1867</unitdate><container id="aspace_3a6db40ffcb094aa6b80311c3d5b0426" label="Mixed Materials [31924066575477]" type="box">1</container><container id="aspace_c6e7ecdd636653c56d68fab50d59f378" parent="aspace_3a6db40ffcb094aa6b80311c3d5b0426" type="folder">2</container></did><scopecontent id="aspace_f9dc502adf45a6fb0743a5d9e58076cb"><head>Scope and Contents</head><p>Review of <title>The North-West Peninsula of Iceland</title>.</p></scopecontent></c02><c02 id="aspace_63c29fcc934a173f5659b0988a1105c3" level="item"><did><unittitle><title>London Review</title></unittitle><unitdate calendar="gregorian" era="ce" normal="1867-04-06/1867-04-06">April 6, 1867</unitdate><container id="aspace_860759dd63828da8e50567671f66a1db" label="Mixed Materials [31924066575477]" type="box">1</container><container id="aspace_1272e2602bb78b23ad1754ec851d42b3" parent="aspace_860759dd63828da8e50567671f66a1db" type="folder">2</container></did><scopecontent id="aspace_9eea8f95e788e979928650d4f14b9544"><head>Scope and Contents</head><p>Review of <title>The North-West Peninsula of Iceland</title>.</p></scopecontent></c02><c02 id="aspace_55ed0d00a304c918812cf0472e3eec51" level="item"><did><unittitle><title>The Spectator</title></unittitle><unitdate calendar="gregorian" era="ce" normal="1867-04-20/1867-04-20">April 20, 1867</unitdate><container id="aspace_91ffa93087e871bb239c3472ff642c67" label="Mixed Materials [31924066575477]" type="box">1</container><container id="aspace_0db0dbdabe67732124fdd41ba518d594" parent="aspace_91ffa93087e871bb239c3472ff642c67" type="folder">2</container></did><scopecontent id="aspace_84797fd72b56511f1188a8472f6bc028"><head>Scope and Contents</head><p>Review of The St. Stephen's Chronicle, The Sorrows of Hypsipyle, The Wife's Litany and Other Pieces in Verse, A Dictionary of Photography, Sunshine and Showers, Prose Works of John Greenleaf Whittier, Germany from the Baltic to the Adriatic; or Prussia, Austria, and Venetia, with Reference to the Late War, The North-West Peninsula of Iceland, being the Journal of a Tour in Iceland in the Spring and Summer of 1862, The Law of Libel, as Affecting the Newspaper Press, with proposed Amendments, The Aeneis of Virgil, Zaida's Nursery Notebook, for the Use of Mothers, Pity, Man: A Story of Light and Darkness, Practical Housekeeping, or the Duties of a Homewife, Maxon's Standard Penny Readings, Africa. Prussia, How to Study the New Testament, and Dan's Treasure; or, Labour and Love.</p></scopecontent></c02><c02 id="aspace_d2aab4fa43ba2b9b6b0dde9