ittitle><unitdate calendar="gregorian" era="ce" normal="1867-05-30/1867-05-30">May 30, 1867</unitdate><container id="aspace_658f5d4254af1136ffbd55de6a53b2ff" label="Mixed Materials [31924088320639]" type="mapcase folder">1</container></did><scopecontent id="aspace_407e52972cb62146c67418b113a100e3"><head>Scope and Contents</head><p>Among many others, contains a review of <title>The North-West Peninsula of Iceland</title>.</p></scopecontent></c02><c02 id="aspace_64a2afd1399b35370718e9538243fec6" level="item"><did><unittitle><title>The Times</title></unittitle><unitdate calendar="gregorian" era="ce" normal="1867-06-06/1867-06-06">June 6, 1867</unitdate><container id="aspace_32c539f7eaa4aa9871d3de5109b1a220" label="Mixed Materials [31924088320639]" type="mapcase folder">1</container></did><scopecontent id="aspace_f50be292ce3639ee285554e2ffe51e48"><head>Scope and Contents</head><p>Among many others, contains a review of <title>The North-West Peninsula of Iceland</title>.</p></scopecontent></c02></c01><c01 id="aspace_a4eadb3d41f3cf9431dcce44fb1bc4a2" level="series"><did><unittitle>Series III. Bound Manuscripts</unittitle></did><c02 id="aspace_73ac7070faac2fedc08d49c97a266f3e" level="item"><did><unittitle>Travel Journal of C. W. Shepherd</unittitle><unitid>Item 14</unitid><unitdate calendar="gregorian" era="ce" normal="1862-04-19/1862-06-27" type="inclusive">April 19, 1862 - June 27, 1862</unitdate><container id="aspace_3041c85b0719edee3d893aaba39a2e98" label="Mixed Materials [31924066575477]" type="box">1</container></did><scopecontent id="aspace_6a7dc6e2ef6a89ed617b33dcf1ae41dd"><head>Scope and Contents</head><p>Rough travel itinerary on first page from April 19th to the end of June; writing begins May 2, ends Friday, June 27; 116 pages of writing.</p></scopecontent></c02><c02 id="aspace_f87e6e2264a843aaa9660b1b618b5939" level="item"><did><unittitle>Travel journal of H. M. Upchev</unittitle><unitid>Item 15</unitid><unitdate calendar="gregorian" era="ce" normal="1862-04-19/1862-07-30" type="inclusive">April 19, 1862 - July 30, 1862</unitdate><container id="aspace_2d1558b84a1446334dfba250551e8c57" label="Mixed Materials [31924066575477]" type="box">1</container></did><scopecontent id="aspace_4b88a71b6ac8c79b35e645ff103dafad"><head>Scope and Contents</head><p>Black cover. Has rough itineraries from April to August (writing appears to be from April to July); begins with April 19, 1862; has a plant stuck between its last few pages.</p></scopecontent></c02><c02 id="aspace_875dc73444e53f89c82f81ef9224857e" level="item"><did><unittitle>Small black notepad</unittitle><unitid>Item 16</unitid><unitdate calendar="gregorian" era="ce" normal="1862-04-28/1862-07-29" type="inclusive">April 28, 1862 - July 29, 1862</unitdate><container id="aspace_624c3afdd33b7848b2819443d0e2d8f2" label="Mixed Materials [31924066575477]" type="box">1</container></did><scopecontent id="aspace_70a07f248042e895f106826be52bf10e"><head>Scope and Contents</head><p>Includes advertisement for the 1862 Royal Mail Steam Ship from Reykjavik to Copenhagen; starting in April, very faded notes on travel (including weather); continues to July; Jack Shepherd written on back cover.</p></scopecontent></c02><c02 id="aspace_c790ca3698b1d33bb1a671092461266c" level="item"><did><unittitle>Journal with red cover</unittitle><unitid>Item 17</unitid><unitdate calendar="gregorian" certainty="questionable" era="ce">July 17 186? - October 3</unitdate><unitdate calendar="gregorian" era="ce">186??</unitdate><container id="aspace_a642bd252fd112424359f7a0d1b0d41a" label="Mixed Materials [31924066575477]" type="box">1</container></did><scopecontent id="aspace_97d691097fbe7a78cd984e4ec74571aa"><head>Scope and Contents</head><p>Front inside cover has a rudimentary travel itinerary for July and August; back inside cover continues to September and up until October 3; 123 written pages; begins with leaving London on July 17 ,ends with September 3 with what should be Mývatn based on the itinerary; the journal records details of travel and the landscapes.</p></scopecontent></c02><c02 id="aspace_4afe083ec1b2a6ebf2f0ecdef381976c" level="item"><did><unittitle>Small black wallet/purse with writings</unittitle><unitid>Item 18</unitid><container id="aspace_330faf0d3acf5bede9560e63749f2131" label="Mixed Materials [31924066575477]" type="box">1</container></did><scopecontent id="aspace_6e85d1954430352e14937ae50658e370"><head>Scope and Contents</head><p>Only fragmentary papers (baggage ticket from Marseilles, some papers with names, Shepherd is mentioned).</p></scopecontent></c02></c01><c01 id="aspace_5c5dc6aef71a3299a34cfa7740225f35" level="series"><did><unittitle>Series iV. Additional Material</unittitle></did><c02 id="aspace_00fef8859a221c86a51d4b12b4b0f646" level="item"><did><unittitle><title>The North-West Peninsula of Iceland: Being the Journal of a Tour in Iceland in the Spring and Summer of 1862</title></unittitle><unitid>Item 19</unitid><unitdate calendar="gregorian" era="ce" normal="1867/1867">1867</unitdate><container id="aspace_619cbd0f4565c954dd14b2c221523be0" label="Mixed Materials [31924066575477]" type="box">1</container></did><scopecontent id="aspace_9ec57d8f9f8b38b6da307419efec19b6"><head>Scope and Contents</head><p>By C. W. Shepherd, M.A., F.Z.S., published in London 1867 by Longmans, Green, and Co.; has a green cover.</p></scopecontent></c02><c02 id="aspace_5c5b7e56ccdac9bf93de742011c29e31" level="item"><did><unittitle>Pages from <title>The North-West Peninsula of Iceland</title></unittitle><unitid>Item 20</unitid><unitdate calendar="gregorian" era="ce" normal="1867/1867">1867</unitdate><container id="aspace_b1098c431e711384d3ec262374e23618" label="Mixed Materials [31924066575477]" type="box">1</container><container id="aspace_257df9377c78c6e128e5b2f2ec7e4060" parent="aspace_b1098c431e711384d3ec262374e23618" type="folder">2</container></did></c02><c02 id="aspace_194eb306c9b9785cdde2d3df58177453" level="item"><did><unittitle>Goða-Foss painting</unittitle><container id="aspace_30b1bab4fb115feed80b286e561a728a" label="Mixed Materials [31924088320639]" type="mapcase folder">1</container></did><scopecontent id="aspace_3e520f78d070c4c675eacb8a7c1e10b8"><head>Scope and Contents</head><p>1A - Rendering of landscape featuring waterfalls and mountains, two figures perched to the top left</p></scopecontent></c02><c02 id="aspace_1d42c411e466d632a32558a980a77e88" level="item"><did><unittitle>Ísa-Fjörðr Town painting</unittitle><container id="aspace_30250b943186b45196c72d15d055460d" label="Mixed Materials [31924088320639]" type="mapcase folder">1</container></did><scopecontent id="aspace_ceef19783a82b1e7d691f37f60893af5"><head>Scope and Contents</head><p>1B - Depicts a stretch of land cutting across a fjord; three boats to the right, several small houses on the land-bridge</p></scopecontent></c02><c02 id="aspace_e79df98faac783ca31ce27832935ea93" level="subseries"><did><unittitle>Uppdráttr Íslands (Carte d'Islande) by Olafs Nikolas Olsens</unittitle><unitdate calendar="gregorian" era="ce" normal="1844/1844">1844</unitdate><container id="aspace_a020c2bbaec7d62976746e7cc80d6e09" label="Mixed Materials [31924088320639]" type="mapcase folder">1</container></did><c03 id="aspace_5382e4be03a073f7b11b33e31aa7eec7" level="item"><did><unittitle>Title page describing the four maps in Icelandic and French)</unittitle><unitdate calendar="gregorian" era="ce" normal="1844/1844">1844</unitdate><container id="aspace_9657d44107b2aec58d41fa2bd6c4e2b3" label="Mixed Materials [31924088320639]" type="mapcase folder">1</container></did></c03><c03 id="aspace_10a684255d651b4fbec3fdd0ecc2dd81" level="item"><did><unittitle>No. 1, Map of Iceland (Ísland: Suðvestr - Fjórðúngr)</unittitle><unitdate calendar="gregorian" era="ce" normal="1844/1844">1844</unitdate><container id="aspace_63fef8337d2f00b0d7f0e497579a9e76" label="Mixed Materials [31924088320639]" type="mapcase folder">1</container></did></c03><c03 id="aspace_6aa53366b1ba4d876d2bc6ffd2f12983" level="ite